1
00:00:09,001 --> 00:00:11,161
[Episode 2]

2
00:00:27,041 --> 00:00:29,291
Excuse me. I'm sorry to ask,

3
00:00:29,381 --> 00:00:31,621
but how can I get to the town center?

4
00:00:31,751 --> 00:00:33,421
It's quite the distance.

5
00:00:33,951 --> 00:00:36,281
Walk straight down that road.

6
00:00:37,961 --> 00:00:39,801
-Thank you.
-No problem.

7
00:00:39,891 --> 00:00:41,261
Good job today.

8
00:00:41,341 --> 00:00:43,191
-Take care.
-You too.

9
00:00:51,551 --> 00:00:54,541
If only you were given a better owner.

10
00:01:01,761 --> 00:01:02,901
Let's get going then.

11
00:01:20,151 --> 00:01:21,080
Here.

12
00:01:21,871 --> 00:01:23,191
Go ahead.

13
00:01:34,411 --> 00:01:36,121
They're always so fast to leave sets.

14
00:01:39,341 --> 00:01:40,661
-Dae-gwon.
-What?

15
00:01:44,621 --> 00:01:45,851
They found out again?

16
00:01:44,621 --> 00:01:46,111
[I love how sexy you are
and how you love me.]

17
00:01:46,201 --> 00:01:48,711
[Why did you change your number?
You should've at least told me.]

18
00:01:46,241 --> 00:01:48,091
It didn't even last six months.

19
00:01:48,711 --> 00:01:49,941
I'm exhausted.

20
00:01:52,451 --> 00:01:53,641
I'll change your number right away.

21
00:01:53,721 --> 00:01:56,321
Let's get going so that
you can rest for the interview tomorrow.

22
00:01:57,071 --> 00:01:58,261
Thanks.

23
00:01:58,341 --> 00:01:59,711
-Hop in.
-Sure.

24
00:02:02,081 --> 00:02:03,621
Don't forget your seat belt.

25
00:02:33,411 --> 00:02:34,511
What on earth?

26
00:02:40,891 --> 00:02:43,051
Dae-gwon, what on earth was that?

27
00:02:44,631 --> 00:02:46,701
People did mention something about ghosts.

28
00:02:46,791 --> 00:02:48,021
What ghosts?

29
00:02:48,111 --> 00:02:49,951
Check it out for me. Go on.

30
00:02:50,311 --> 00:02:51,851
But you're my manager.

31
00:02:51,931 --> 00:02:54,881
You! Well, you earn more than I do.

32
00:02:55,501 --> 00:02:56,771
Go on.

33
00:03:00,031 --> 00:03:01,751
What is it? What do you see?

34
00:03:02,011 --> 00:03:04,121
Nothing. I don't see a thing.

35
00:03:04,211 --> 00:03:05,311
Really?

36
00:03:15,251 --> 00:03:17,631
-What? Why?
-Something's there.

37
00:03:21,721 --> 00:03:24,141
-It's her.
-You're making no sense.

38
00:03:24,851 --> 00:03:26,650
The kisaeng you slashed to death.

39
00:03:30,871 --> 00:03:32,991
I heard a manager left his actor behind.

40
00:03:33,071 --> 00:03:35,451
-Was he hers?
-What do you mean?

41
00:03:35,541 --> 00:03:37,081
One of the managers ran off.

42
00:03:37,521 --> 00:03:39,101
I've seen those fleeing

43
00:03:39,191 --> 00:03:41,351
while leaving their cars behind,

44
00:03:41,431 --> 00:03:43,771
but one leaving in the car is a first.

45
00:03:48,521 --> 00:03:51,111
Hey, back up.

46
00:03:53,311 --> 00:03:55,211
To give her a ride? No way.

47
00:03:55,291 --> 00:03:57,101
-Why not?
-You know the agency's policy.

48
00:03:57,191 --> 00:03:58,811
-No.
-Come on.

49
00:04:27,721 --> 00:04:28,821
Hello.

50
00:04:30,541 --> 00:04:31,811
-Get in.
-Sorry?

51
00:04:35,111 --> 00:04:36,651
No, I'm good.

52
00:04:36,741 --> 00:04:40,921
The town center is right past that hill.
I'll get there in no time.

53
00:04:41,181 --> 00:04:43,031
Which is why you should hop in.

54
00:04:48,141 --> 00:04:50,071
I know well being in the industry myself.

55
00:04:50,161 --> 00:04:52,181
We're not supposed to give people a ride.

56
00:04:52,801 --> 00:04:55,401
I don't want to bother you
with something this trivial.

57
00:04:55,921 --> 00:04:57,771
The offer was more than enough.

58
00:04:58,701 --> 00:04:59,801
Good night.

59
00:05:13,831 --> 00:05:15,811
You'll catch a cold once your sweat cools.

60
00:05:18,411 --> 00:05:19,641
Hold on.

61
00:05:20,611 --> 00:05:22,191
If this is because of earlier,

62
00:05:22,281 --> 00:05:24,441
there's no need to be bothered.

63
00:05:24,521 --> 00:05:27,471
This is me wanting to walk,
so go about your own way.

64
00:05:28,841 --> 00:05:30,071
Copycat.

65
00:05:34,601 --> 00:05:37,421
Wait. He knew?

66
00:05:39,841 --> 00:05:41,071
Darn, it's cold.

67
00:05:45,071 --> 00:05:47,841
[7 years ago]

68
00:05:45,201 --> 00:05:46,881
Do you perhaps know Stevie Wonder?

69
00:05:47,931 --> 00:05:50,441
He sang "I Just Called to Say I Love You"

70
00:05:52,071 --> 00:05:54,271
and is my dad's favorite artist.

71
00:05:56,201 --> 00:05:58,931
I once saw him on TV, you know.

72
00:06:00,031 --> 00:06:03,461
Despite being visually impaired,
he writes songs and even sings.

73
00:06:05,361 --> 00:06:07,201
On that show, he said this.

74
00:06:09,101 --> 00:06:12,001
We were all born with unique talents.

75
00:06:12,531 --> 00:06:14,331
The only difference between us

76
00:06:14,421 --> 00:06:19,391
"is that some make use of it
while some don't."

77
00:06:23,621 --> 00:06:25,551
And this is what my dad said right after.

78
00:06:26,701 --> 00:06:27,841
Ma-ha,

79
00:06:29,381 --> 00:06:31,891
"I hope you live your life
the way he does."

80
00:06:35,191 --> 00:06:38,221
So you came to our dance team
to utilize your talent?

81
00:06:41,081 --> 00:06:42,181
Yes.

82
00:06:43,021 --> 00:06:45,531
I'm thinking about moving to Seoul too.

83
00:06:46,631 --> 00:06:48,391
I doubt he'll approve of that.

84
00:06:57,011 --> 00:06:58,601
You will. Won't you, Dad?

85
00:07:05,851 --> 00:07:07,611
Seoul's too bright even at night

86
00:07:09,681 --> 00:07:11,091
to properly see the stars.

87
00:07:13,111 --> 00:07:14,480
That's the only downside.

88
00:07:25,741 --> 00:07:27,021
I can see a lot of stars today.

89
00:07:38,501 --> 00:07:40,831
When did you figure it out?

90
00:07:41,411 --> 00:07:42,771
When you started to avoid me.

91
00:07:43,431 --> 00:07:45,541
No, I wasn't avoiding you at all.

92
00:07:45,631 --> 00:07:47,081
Only stay at my heel.

93
00:07:50,871 --> 00:07:51,881
Got it.

94
00:07:51,971 --> 00:07:54,651
He'll come running over
if he senses that something's up.

95
00:08:10,230 --> 00:08:12,471
Well, we're here.

96
00:08:17,401 --> 00:08:18,591
It's still cold outside.

97
00:08:30,111 --> 00:08:31,871
Will you be okay from here?

98
00:08:32,621 --> 00:08:34,341
Yes, I can find my own way now.

99
00:08:39,221 --> 00:08:40,721
A friend will pick me up.

100
00:08:50,131 --> 00:08:51,891
We should've just let her get in.

101
00:08:52,911 --> 00:08:55,681
She didn't want to
and there's the agency policy.

102
00:08:56,821 --> 00:08:58,981
You know I never go against
the boss' words.

103
00:09:00,031 --> 00:09:01,221
As if.

104
00:09:16,931 --> 00:09:18,071
I'm such an idiot.

105
00:09:18,651 --> 00:09:21,151
-Dae-gwon, can you slow down?
-Sure.

106
00:09:42,711 --> 00:09:44,251
What's happening?

107
00:09:47,951 --> 00:09:49,091
Ma-ha!

108
00:09:50,851 --> 00:09:52,831
No wonder she refused to get in.

109
00:09:53,841 --> 00:09:54,721
What on earth?

110
00:09:55,601 --> 00:09:57,671
-Yu-jin?
-Are you hurt?

111
00:09:58,331 --> 00:09:59,611
No, I'm good.

112
00:09:59,701 --> 00:10:01,761
How did you know to get here?

113
00:10:03,261 --> 00:10:05,811
I'm glad. What a relief.

114
00:10:12,411 --> 00:10:13,731
Dae-gwon, I'm tired.

115
00:10:14,961 --> 00:10:17,121
-Can we hurry home?
-Sure.

116
00:10:27,461 --> 00:10:28,471
[3:04 a.m.]

117
00:10:33,971 --> 00:10:35,561
How did you know to get here though?

118
00:10:37,451 --> 00:10:38,991
[Hello? Hey, Yu-jin.]

119
00:10:39,871 --> 00:10:41,321
I can't get a hold of Ma-ha.

120
00:10:41,411 --> 00:10:42,951
Maybe she's busy filming.

121
00:10:43,041 --> 00:10:44,441
I can't reach our manager either.

122
00:10:44,801 --> 00:10:46,291
[It just doesn't make any sense.]

123
00:10:46,381 --> 00:10:48,671
-Could something be up?
-Let's hang up for now.

124
00:10:50,821 --> 00:10:52,671
[Ma-ha]

125
00:10:58,741 --> 00:11:00,111
[Ma-ha]

126
00:11:04,021 --> 00:11:06,001
[Ma-ha]

127
00:11:15,161 --> 00:11:17,531
[I suddenly got a movie shooting.
I'm on my way to Mungyeong.]

128
00:11:29,241 --> 00:11:31,961
Were you that worried about me?

129
00:11:34,031 --> 00:11:35,661
Nothing beats a good friend.

130
00:11:36,541 --> 00:11:38,831
-My soulmate.
-It was quite the distance

131
00:11:39,621 --> 00:11:41,511
and was dangerous to walk alone.

132
00:11:42,441 --> 00:11:43,711
I ran the whole length

133
00:11:44,771 --> 00:11:47,321
feeling the cool and refreshing breeze.

134
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:50,531
The stars kept me company too.

135
00:11:51,851 --> 00:11:55,281
Wasn't there anyone
who offered you a lift?

136
00:11:56,601 --> 00:11:58,141
There was,

137
00:12:00,611 --> 00:12:02,591
but it would've only complicated things.

138
00:12:03,861 --> 00:12:06,241
I wouldn't have been as comfortable
as I am with you.

139
00:12:07,511 --> 00:12:10,811
Whatever. I still can't believe
what your manager did.

140
00:12:11,561 --> 00:12:13,101
How can he leave you stranded?

141
00:12:13,941 --> 00:12:15,131
You should report him.

142
00:12:15,211 --> 00:12:16,931
He shouldn't get away with this.

143
00:12:17,631 --> 00:12:19,701
He'll only do this again to someone else.

144
00:12:19,791 --> 00:12:23,271
Forget it. I'm the one
who didn't want to let go.

145
00:12:24,151 --> 00:12:25,771
Besides, he's not a bad person.

146
00:12:27,141 --> 00:12:29,601
I bet he's overwhelmed
with guilt right now.

147
00:12:33,121 --> 00:12:35,851
Wait. But what if you get caught?

148
00:12:38,971 --> 00:12:40,161
It'll be fine.

149
00:12:40,911 --> 00:12:42,801
You should get some sleep.
I bet you're tired.

150
00:12:43,331 --> 00:12:44,471
Maybe I will.

151
00:12:56,181 --> 00:12:57,451
[SHAX]

152
00:12:59,651 --> 00:13:00,841
SHAX?

153
00:13:34,681 --> 00:13:35,651
What?

154
00:13:37,231 --> 00:13:39,211
When did we get here?
You should've woken me up.

155
00:13:46,651 --> 00:13:48,491
Hyun-ji, you're here too.

156
00:13:48,581 --> 00:13:51,001
I got worried
when you couldn't be reached.

157
00:13:51,881 --> 00:13:53,071
Are you all right?

158
00:13:54,131 --> 00:13:55,271
Yes, I'm good.

159
00:13:57,121 --> 00:13:58,921
Yu-jin, you'll be late. Get going.

160
00:13:59,011 --> 00:14:01,741
-Sure. Get some rest.
-Okay.

161
00:14:04,511 --> 00:14:06,531
Thanks for last night
and be safe on the road.

162
00:14:06,621 --> 00:14:07,681
Got it.

163
00:14:10,271 --> 00:14:11,811
-Bye.
-Drive safely.

164
00:14:11,901 --> 00:14:13,131
-Let's go.
-Come on.

165
00:14:17,231 --> 00:14:18,991
-Let's go.
-Sure.

166
00:14:34,691 --> 00:14:37,731
Where did you go last night
in the manager's van?

167
00:14:37,821 --> 00:14:38,741
I'm sorry.

168
00:14:38,831 --> 00:14:41,201
Forget the apologies
and tell me where you went!

169
00:14:42,661 --> 00:14:44,111
Were you out with a girl?

170
00:14:45,161 --> 00:14:48,071
Hold on. His silence says it all.

171
00:14:49,171 --> 00:14:50,311
So tell me.

172
00:14:50,401 --> 00:14:52,861
Are you seeking fun
since we have no fans that watch us?

173
00:14:53,301 --> 00:14:54,671
What about the others then?

174
00:14:54,761 --> 00:14:57,311
Do you think we stay locked up
because we have nowhere to go?

175
00:14:58,801 --> 00:15:00,261
This won't happen again.

176
00:15:01,271 --> 00:15:03,641
-I'm sorry.
-Get a grip on yourself.

177
00:15:04,081 --> 00:15:06,331
You know how crucial our next album is.

178
00:15:06,811 --> 00:15:08,441
Who knows what'll happen

179
00:15:08,531 --> 00:15:10,201
if it doesn't stir up any response?

180
00:15:20,891 --> 00:15:23,531
Let's head inside. Come on.

181
00:15:28,551 --> 00:15:30,881
-Hyeon-o, that's enough.
-He gets on my nerves.

182
00:15:31,721 --> 00:15:33,611
So much for the boy scout act.

183
00:15:35,941 --> 00:15:37,921
Where the heck did he go anyway?

184
00:15:38,581 --> 00:15:39,941
Weren't you scared?

185
00:15:40,471 --> 00:15:41,791
What did I tell you?

186
00:15:41,881 --> 00:15:44,261
I knew he was one
to throw people under buses.

187
00:15:45,711 --> 00:15:48,221
You should've left the agency when we did.

188
00:15:48,441 --> 00:15:52,131
I knew I was being used
to cash in on smaller gigs.

189
00:15:52,401 --> 00:15:54,071
But you still went along with it?

190
00:15:54,161 --> 00:15:55,301
Well,

191
00:15:56,531 --> 00:15:58,561
I guess I didn't want to let go.

192
00:15:59,001 --> 00:16:03,221
Because once I do,
I knew it'd be out of my reach.

193
00:16:03,311 --> 00:16:05,771
How one can leave you behind baffles me.

194
00:16:08,501 --> 00:16:11,491
Do you know why I was upset and terrified

195
00:16:12,461 --> 00:16:14,921
while walking down from the woods?

196
00:16:16,201 --> 00:16:18,271
It's because I knew

197
00:16:19,721 --> 00:16:21,391
that my lifeline had been severed.

198
00:16:32,131 --> 00:16:34,331
[I finally saw my place in this world.]

199
00:16:35,031 --> 00:16:37,281
What I've always dreamed of

200
00:16:37,890 --> 00:16:40,711
seemed well within my reach,

201
00:16:42,071 --> 00:16:43,571
but I couldn't quite grab it.

202
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:47,001
For some reason, I kept looking behind me.

203
00:16:48,801 --> 00:16:50,650
It made me feel worse.

204
00:16:52,680 --> 00:16:54,041
This must be the end for me.

205
00:16:56,021 --> 00:16:58,481
I made up my mind on my way back here.

206
00:16:59,981 --> 00:17:01,211
I'm quitting.

207
00:17:02,001 --> 00:17:03,891
I think I've tried enough.

208
00:17:05,171 --> 00:17:06,801
I'd rather get my GED.

209
00:17:08,341 --> 00:17:09,831
-Ma-ha!
-Hey.

210
00:17:13,441 --> 00:17:15,201
We're only 22.

211
00:17:16,921 --> 00:17:19,511
In the K-pop industry,
we're considered old,

212
00:17:20,091 --> 00:17:21,581
but not out in the rest of the world.

213
00:17:22,951 --> 00:17:24,621
We're young enough
to try whatever we want.

214
00:17:25,941 --> 00:17:28,671
You're right. I'm quitting with you.

215
00:17:29,241 --> 00:17:30,471
You too?

216
00:17:30,561 --> 00:17:34,081
I went to sing at a wedding yesterday
and ended up feeling sorry for myself.

217
00:17:34,251 --> 00:17:36,371
Reality hit me hard.

218
00:17:37,551 --> 00:17:40,721
As a kid, my grandma would take me

219
00:17:40,811 --> 00:17:44,811
to sing for families
hosting parties and events.

220
00:17:47,281 --> 00:17:50,091
It struck me that
nothing had changed for me.

221
00:17:51,281 --> 00:17:54,931
Is this what I get
for working my butt off?

222
00:17:56,651 --> 00:17:59,251
Fine. I'm quitting too.

223
00:18:00,571 --> 00:18:02,721
I grew up hearing I was pretty,

224
00:18:03,601 --> 00:18:05,711
so I thought I really was.

225
00:18:07,121 --> 00:18:09,281
But here,
I'm just another above-average face.

226
00:18:11,521 --> 00:18:13,851
Living in a bubble as a queen

227
00:18:14,781 --> 00:18:16,711
must've been the peak of my life.

228
00:18:19,311 --> 00:18:21,421
I'm not as talented as you two are.

229
00:18:22,921 --> 00:18:24,281
Don't say that.

230
00:18:24,371 --> 00:18:26,571
That's enough. Stop crying.

231
00:18:27,581 --> 00:18:31,851
70,080 hours. 2,920 days.

232
00:18:33,301 --> 00:18:34,401
Eight years.

233
00:18:35,631 --> 00:18:37,091
I'm sick and tired of it now.

234
00:18:37,531 --> 00:18:40,471
As of tomorrow, I'm starting a new life.

235
00:18:41,271 --> 00:18:42,371
Reboot!

236
00:18:53,011 --> 00:18:54,471
-Devil SHAX.
-Devil SHAX.

237
00:18:54,551 --> 00:18:56,231
-Hello, we're SHAX.
-Hello, we're SHAX.

238
00:19:03,351 --> 00:19:04,451
Ryok,

239
00:19:04,541 --> 00:19:07,271
I hear your new project is a period movie.

240
00:19:07,581 --> 00:19:11,711
I was worried at first
since the genre is foreign to me.

241
00:19:12,151 --> 00:19:15,541
So I've been channeling
the rookie actor I used to be

242
00:19:15,631 --> 00:19:17,791
by practicing my tone and fight scenes.

243
00:19:18,181 --> 00:19:21,881
Well, I'm curious as to
what we can look forward to from you.

244
00:19:21,971 --> 00:19:25,221
I'd appreciate it
if you checked it out in theaters.

245
00:19:25,841 --> 00:19:28,571
Lastly, could you tell us how it feels to

246
00:19:28,651 --> 00:19:30,541
celebrate SHAX's sixth year?

247
00:19:31,511 --> 00:19:34,941
I was the last one to talk,
so why don't I go first?

248
00:19:40,661 --> 00:19:45,331
Individually, we lack in many ways
and have a number of flaws.

249
00:19:45,991 --> 00:19:48,581
I hope we can continue
to complete one another

250
00:19:48,671 --> 00:19:50,831
for ten, maybe 20...

251
00:19:51,221 --> 00:19:52,321
Actually,

252
00:19:53,031 --> 00:19:55,581
until the day we die.

253
00:19:56,281 --> 00:19:58,311
Isn't SHAX originally a six-piece group?

254
00:20:00,951 --> 00:20:05,391
Many are still wondering about
what happened to Eun-jo.

255
00:20:05,481 --> 00:20:08,431
Is there no possibility of him returning?

256
00:20:08,521 --> 00:20:11,241
Please stick to the approved questions.

257
00:20:11,331 --> 00:20:13,621
You were the closest to Eun-jo.

258
00:20:13,711 --> 00:20:15,071
Are you not in touch?

259
00:20:16,221 --> 00:20:18,811
That'll be all for today's interview.
Thank you.

260
00:20:23,831 --> 00:20:24,971
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

261
00:20:28,761 --> 00:20:29,861
Good work.

262
00:20:45,431 --> 00:20:47,191
