[GED Exam Academy]

303
00:25:04,281 --> 00:25:06,521
[2020 GED, Korean, English, Math]

304
00:25:06,611 --> 00:25:09,081
[Master the GED Exam!]

305
00:25:27,201 --> 00:25:28,351
Hello?

306
00:25:30,461 --> 00:25:33,231
Oh, right. I see.

307
00:25:34,901 --> 00:25:37,461
I'm sorry. Bye.

308
00:25:50,441 --> 00:25:51,541
Hello?

309
00:25:53,161 --> 00:25:55,671
Yes, I am Lee Ma-ha,

310
00:25:56,161 --> 00:25:57,831
but I'm not interested.

311
00:25:58,401 --> 00:26:00,291
Yes. I'm sorry.

312
00:26:03,861 --> 00:26:07,381
Goodness! Those creative scammers.

313
00:26:10,761 --> 00:26:12,261
[Mahee Hair]

314
00:26:15,781 --> 00:26:17,581
I'm home.

315
00:26:25,861 --> 00:26:28,941
-What about the academy?
-What's with your new hair?

316
00:26:29,991 --> 00:26:31,181
Is it pretty?

317
00:26:31,801 --> 00:26:33,731
I got briefed about the classes for now.

318
00:26:34,921 --> 00:26:38,701
Oh, right. I got a weird call earlier.

319
00:26:39,801 --> 00:26:41,561
JH Entertainment?

320
00:26:42,091 --> 00:26:43,411
The CEO's name is...

321
00:26:43,501 --> 00:26:45,701
-Ji-hak.
-That's right. It's Ji-hak.

322
00:26:45,791 --> 00:26:47,861
-You got his call too?
-Yes.

323
00:26:47,941 --> 00:26:49,221
He's a conman.

324
00:26:49,571 --> 00:26:51,551
I asked him how he got my number,

325
00:26:51,901 --> 00:26:54,461
-and he told me to come for the audition.
-You got his call too?

326
00:26:55,381 --> 00:26:57,801
Those psychos. It's so frustrating.

327
00:26:58,721 --> 00:27:00,751
Maybe it's the new kind of voice phishing.

328
00:27:05,981 --> 00:27:07,521
[Do you want to dream once again?]

329
00:27:07,611 --> 00:27:09,501
[The Renew Audition,
November 1st, 2020, JH Entertainment]

330
00:27:12,851 --> 00:27:14,741
[Music Holic]

331
00:27:14,831 --> 00:27:15,791
[Ma-ha]

332
00:27:19,801 --> 00:27:20,901
[Hey, Yu-jin.]

333
00:27:20,991 --> 00:27:23,101
Hi, Ma-ha. It's been long.

334
00:27:23,191 --> 00:27:25,471
Darn it. Will you focus?

335
00:27:26,051 --> 00:27:27,151
Sorry.

336
00:27:27,231 --> 00:27:30,401
Hello, Tae-geun. Have you been well?

337
00:27:30,491 --> 00:27:34,191
I'm doing okay.
Yu-jin is practicing at the moment.

338
00:27:34,271 --> 00:27:35,771
Then I'll call him again.

339
00:27:35,861 --> 00:27:38,231
That means it's about something
you can't tell me.

340
00:27:38,501 --> 00:27:40,261
Stop calling him if that's what you want.

341
00:27:40,351 --> 00:27:42,191
Sorry? Okay.

342
00:27:42,281 --> 00:27:45,891
Oh, right. Didn't Ji-hak call you?

343
00:27:51,571 --> 00:27:52,891
Okay, thank you.

344
00:27:55,971 --> 00:27:57,641
What is it? Did his manager pick up?

345
00:27:57,731 --> 00:27:59,311
It must be about the last time.

346
00:27:59,401 --> 00:28:00,411
Yes.

347
00:28:01,161 --> 00:28:04,591
About that conman though...

348
00:28:06,001 --> 00:28:07,451
I guess he's not a conman after all.

349
00:28:08,021 --> 00:28:09,871
He used to be a manager at NOG.

350
00:28:11,101 --> 00:28:12,291
NOG?

351
00:28:16,251 --> 00:28:17,261
[The Renew Audition, JH Entertainment]

352
00:28:19,071 --> 00:28:20,831
[The Renew Audition, JH Entertainment]

353
00:28:33,501 --> 00:28:34,911
[JH Entertainment Audition]

354
00:28:34,991 --> 00:28:37,151
[It's open for today.]

355
00:28:37,461 --> 00:28:39,751
The audition is held in a cafe?

356
00:28:39,831 --> 00:28:43,351
I don't care if he was a manager.
I'm sure he's just a conman.

357
00:28:43,441 --> 00:28:45,381
Still, we're here anyway.

358
00:28:47,801 --> 00:28:48,991
Let's go in.

359
00:28:52,151 --> 00:28:53,301
Come on!

360
00:28:55,981 --> 00:28:58,361
I'll go in because I pity myself
for coming all the way here.

361
00:28:59,681 --> 00:29:02,321
Fine. If it's a con,
let's just have some tea.

362
00:29:03,371 --> 00:29:04,521
Let's go.

363
00:29:31,097 --> 00:29:32,197
You came.

364
00:29:34,437 --> 00:29:36,117
The one in the middle is Lee Ma-ha.

365
00:29:36,947 --> 00:29:38,007
You're Yoo Ri-a.

366
00:29:38,097 --> 00:29:40,027
And you're Sim Hyun-ji.

367
00:29:41,217 --> 00:29:43,547
-Yes, that's me.
-Nice to meet you.

368
00:29:43,987 --> 00:29:47,907
I'm the CEO of JH Entertainment
and the owner of this cafe.

369
00:29:47,997 --> 00:29:49,227
I'm Ji-hak.

370
00:29:49,667 --> 00:29:51,117
You're all pros,

371
00:29:51,207 --> 00:29:52,837
so shall we begin when you're ready?

372
00:29:54,197 --> 00:29:58,557
Is it okay if we audition together?

373
00:30:00,007 --> 00:30:02,157
Actually, we didn't come for the audition.

374
00:30:02,907 --> 00:30:04,407
We came to commemorate

375
00:30:05,107 --> 00:30:06,737
the ending of our dream.

376
00:30:08,477 --> 00:30:10,567
Is that so?

377
00:30:10,657 --> 00:30:12,767
-It's a little embarrassing.
-It's our first time.

378
00:30:12,857 --> 00:30:14,837
To perform together as a team.

379
00:30:15,277 --> 00:30:17,557
We were supposed to debut as a team.

380
00:30:17,867 --> 00:30:18,967
Yes.

381
00:30:19,057 --> 00:30:22,267
I know you made your debut
as a three-piece girl group. OMEGA-3.

382
00:30:22,357 --> 00:30:26,007
No, we did not debut.
We were just close to it.

383
00:30:26,097 --> 00:30:29,087
There was an incident
on the day of our debut.

384
00:30:29,177 --> 00:30:31,687
You were dragged out of the stage
during your rehearsal.

385
00:30:32,477 --> 00:30:33,887
I know that too.

386
00:30:41,407 --> 00:30:43,607
[It's really hard to
make idol groups popular these days.]

387
00:30:44,097 --> 00:30:46,907
What are you going to do
with those girls who have nowhere to go?

388
00:30:46,997 --> 00:30:48,477
With your career and discernment...

389
00:30:49,457 --> 00:30:51,177
I'm Ji-hak of NOG.

390
00:30:51,267 --> 00:30:53,027
I'm the manager of SHAX, Ji-hak.

391
00:30:53,117 --> 00:30:54,957
It was those titles.

392
00:30:55,447 --> 00:30:56,497
It wasn't me.

393
00:31:05,437 --> 00:31:07,857
[Sim Hyun-ji]

394
00:31:06,837 --> 00:31:07,477
The trainee

395
00:31:08,907 --> 00:31:11,417
who was kicked out
without getting to debut.

396
00:31:12,477 --> 00:31:17,797
[Ri-a]

397
00:31:16,387 --> 00:31:19,467
The girl who only sang
other singers' songs on their stage.

398
00:31:22,597 --> 00:31:25,897
[Lee Ma-ha]

399
00:31:24,087 --> 00:31:25,807
The girl who only does cheap gigs

400
00:31:25,897 --> 00:31:27,787
and never got to do her own stuff.

401
00:31:31,347 --> 00:31:33,507
They made their debut,

402
00:31:34,827 --> 00:31:37,067
but they fell
to the bottom of their lives.

403
00:31:37,507 --> 00:31:40,987
You need stories to be popular these days.

404
00:31:41,777 --> 00:31:44,287
You know it too.
They're as good as the popular ones.

405
00:31:45,257 --> 00:31:47,717
They don't have those trained smiles.

406
00:31:49,167 --> 00:31:50,887
They'll reveal everything
about themselves.

407
00:31:50,977 --> 00:31:53,127
After that, I'll garner attention on them

408
00:31:54,137 --> 00:31:57,487
with a totally different method
as quickly as I can.

409
00:32:05,187 --> 00:32:07,337
This place is not much of a stage,

410
00:32:07,427 --> 00:32:09,587
but you can go ahead
and commemorate your dream.

411
00:32:14,597 --> 00:32:16,047
-OMEGA-3!
-OMEGA-3!

412
00:32:21,417 --> 00:32:25,727
♫ My baby, my heart is beating so fast ♫

413
00:32:26,037 --> 00:32:27,137
♫ Oh, my ♫

414
00:32:27,227 --> 00:32:31,497
♫ My heart goes pit-a-pat,
it's beating fast ♫

415
00:32:31,587 --> 00:32:33,037
♫ I know it boy ♫

416
00:32:33,127 --> 00:32:36,117
♫ You're perfect for me, you're my type ♫

417
00:32:36,207 --> 00:32:38,977
♫ My eyes are filled with love for you ♫

418
00:32:39,067 --> 00:32:43,197
♫ When the long-waited love
whispers to me ♫

419
00:32:43,287 --> 00:32:45,047
♫ I fall for you ♫

420
00:32:45,527 --> 00:32:50,237
♫ I stare at my phone all day ♫

421
00:32:50,897 --> 00:32:54,327
♫ But I can't express
how much I love you ♫

422
00:32:54,417 --> 00:32:57,327
♫ I wait again, like a fool ♫

423
00:32:58,467 --> 00:33:01,457
♫ My boy, I want to hear
your sweet voice ♫

424
00:33:01,547 --> 00:33:03,657
♫ If I hear your voice ♫

425
00:33:03,747 --> 00:33:05,817
♫ My heart just melts, Ring my bell ♫

426
00:33:05,907 --> 00:33:07,487
♫ Always stay right next to me ♫

427
00:33:07,577 --> 00:33:09,867
♫ You're so handsome, I'm so happy ♫

428
00:33:21,307 --> 00:33:22,977
-Good work.
-That was great.

429
00:33:25,967 --> 00:33:27,637
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

430
00:33:27,947 --> 00:33:30,057
I'd like to work with you three

431
00:33:31,247 --> 00:33:32,387
if it's all right with you.

432
00:33:32,747 --> 00:33:33,757
-What?
-What?

433
00:33:38,727 --> 00:33:40,667
It's giving us a headache, isn't it?

434
00:33:42,997 --> 00:33:45,727
I'm getting scared
because this is all too sudden.

435
00:33:45,806 --> 00:33:47,656
Is it possible

436
00:33:48,007 --> 00:33:50,207
to be the CEO of an agency

437
00:33:50,297 --> 00:33:52,277
and run a cafe at the same time?

438
00:33:52,366 --> 00:33:54,386
I know, right?
Seems like there's no part-timer too.

439
00:33:54,527 --> 00:33:56,727
Exactly. That means he's penniless.

440
00:33:56,806 --> 00:33:57,866
But

441
00:33:59,056 --> 00:34:00,767
when we auditioned,

442
00:34:00,857 --> 00:34:02,837
it seemed like he was sincere.

443
00:34:02,927 --> 00:34:04,207
I agree.

444
00:34:04,287 --> 00:34:07,017
Does that mean you all got convinced?

445
00:34:08,167 --> 00:34:09,127
Nonsense.

446
00:34:09,217 --> 00:34:11,987
I even cut my hair
to show how determined I am.

447
00:34:14,677 --> 00:34:17,927
We won't sign with him anyway,
so why don't we just lay it on?

448
00:34:18,417 --> 00:34:20,217
Like the fantasy of all trainees?

449
00:34:23,346 --> 00:34:26,467
Well, since you wanted
to work with us so much.

450
00:34:26,556 --> 00:34:28,886
Let us tell you our conditions.

451
00:34:29,727 --> 00:34:31,747
Here's the contract I want to suggest.

452
00:34:47,097 --> 00:34:48,417
[Management Exclusive Contract]

453
00:34:48,507 --> 00:34:50,617
[Article 1, Exclusive Management]

454
00:34:50,707 --> 00:34:53,037
[A monthly payment
of 1.82 million won will be given.]

455
00:34:59,907 --> 00:35:02,497
You're going to pay us monthly?

456
00:35:02,587 --> 00:35:05,227
-As soon as we sign with you?
-It doesn't make any sense.

457
00:35:05,317 --> 00:35:09,057
I may be paying you minimum wages,
but if we have more profits,

458
00:35:09,147 --> 00:35:11,957
I'll divide and pay them
according to the contract.

459
00:35:12,047 --> 00:35:13,237
I don't buy it.

460
00:35:13,327 --> 00:35:15,477
Are you a conman, by any chance?

461
00:35:15,567 --> 00:35:18,167
Would I say I am if I were one?

462
00:35:18,257 --> 00:35:21,027
You're not going to make us
do anything weird, are you?

463
00:35:22,877 --> 00:35:26,477
"If the employer asks the employee
to do something extreme,"

464
00:35:26,567 --> 00:35:29,997
"the employee can receive
a penalty for breach of contract."

465
00:35:31,407 --> 00:35:34,977
You're not banning us from
using our phones, going outside,

466
00:35:35,057 --> 00:35:36,377
or dating?

467
00:35:37,567 --> 00:35:40,117
You know well
that those things can't be stopped.

468
00:35:40,387 --> 00:35:42,717
Just remember
that actions come with consequences.

469
00:35:42,807 --> 00:35:45,267
You need to take responsibility
for your own action.

470
00:35:56,137 --> 00:35:57,637
Excuse me.

471
00:35:58,427 --> 00:35:59,657
Hello, welcome!

472
00:36:06,657 --> 00:36:07,667
Come with me.

473
00:36:12,017 --> 00:36:13,477
I was going to drive a hard bargain.

474
00:36:13,557 --> 00:36:16,117
But his was even harder
that I couldn't even suggest anything.

475
00:36:16,197 --> 00:36:17,217
What do you want to do?

476
00:36:17,697 --> 00:36:19,457
I'm all convinced, but...

477
00:36:20,557 --> 00:36:22,627
Even so, this doesn't make any sense.

478
00:36:20,557 --> 00:36:22,627
[Management Contract]

479
00:36:22,717 --> 00:36:25,967
Maybe it's because we've never
had such a contract. It does make sense.

480
00:36:26,057 --> 00:36:28,387
In Japan, celebrities receive
a monthly payment.

481
00:36:28,607 --> 00:36:30,147
We've seen a lot of people who struggled

482
00:36:30,237 --> 00:36:31,867
after signing a wrongful contract.

483
00:36:32,967 --> 00:36:35,167
The duration of the contract is a year.

484
00:36:35,257 --> 00:36:37,627
That's all I can afford, actually.

485
00:36:38,377 --> 00:36:40,397
If it doesn't seem to work out,

486
00:36:40,487 --> 00:36:41,807
we can cancel our contract.

487
00:36:41,897 --> 00:36:44,447
What if we make it big?

488
00:36:44,537 --> 00:36:47,527
Then we'll write up a new contract,
satisfying each party's conditions.

489
00:36:47,877 --> 00:36:50,477
That's only if you want to.

490
00:36:50,567 --> 00:36:52,857
-Excuse me!
-Coming!

491
00:36:52,807 --> 00:36:58,707
[H Cafe]

492
00:36:58,797 --> 00:36:59,807
It's only a year.

493
00:37:01,297 --> 00:37:02,317
Just one more year.

494
00:37:03,547 --> 00:37:04,907
I want to extend my dream

495
00:37:05,877 --> 00:37:07,807
by just a year.

496
00:37:09,437 --> 00:37:13,087
Fine. Let's just take a chance
and extend it by a year.

497
00:37:14,937 --> 00:37:16,967
We have nothing to lose anyway.

498
00:37:17,487 --> 00:37:19,117
Okay, then.

499
00:37:19,867 --> 00:37:20,837
Let's do it.

500
00:37:26,507 --> 00:37:27,967
[Lee Ma-ha]

501
00:37:31,567 --> 00:37:32,537
[Yoo Ri-a]

502
00:37:38,787 --> 00:37:39,887
[Management Contract]

503
00:37:43,007 --> 00:37:45,607
Just like you said,
we have nothing to lose.

504
00:37:45,957 --> 00:37:48,337
So let's trust each other
and work together.

505
00:37:49,387 --> 00:37:51,807
Then what should we do first?

506
00:37:51,897 --> 00:37:54,187
You didn't read
your contract thoroughly, did you?

507
00:37:54,317 --> 00:37:56,787
Your contract starts tomorrow.

508
00:37:56,867 --> 00:37:59,727
You can go home and rest today

509
00:37:59,817 --> 00:38:01,317
since you'll become busy soon.

510
00:38:13,327 --> 00:38:14,467
Thank you for this.

511
00:38:14,557 --> 00:38:16,447
-Thank you for this.
-Sure.

512
00:38:16,537 --> 00:38:18,387
It's another beginning
starting from tomorrow.

513
00:38:18,917 --> 00:38:21,997
Maybe we should come up
with a new group name.

514
00:38:24,547 --> 00:38:26,437
-With a new mindset.
-With a new mindset.

515
00:38:31,497 --> 00:38:32,727
How should we name ourselves?

516
00:38:34,007 --> 00:38:35,417
-Gosh, it's hot!
-Be careful.

517
00:38:35,507 --> 00:38:36,827
Cool it down and drink it slowly.

518
00:39:16,207 --> 00:39:17,217
-Tea Party?
-Tea Party?

519
00:39:17,307 --> 00:39:19,107
